# Project: GameSage — Game Mastery App
# Purpose: Stateful, multi-step AI coaching agent for gamers. RAG-powered FastAPI API
#          that assesses player weaknesses, retrieves targeted strategy content from Qdrant,
#          and generates personalised 7-day coaching plans. Portfolio project — not production grade.
#          Goal: learn AI engineering deeply and demonstrate it in SDE interviews.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = LANGUAGE & FRAMEWORK =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Language: Python 3.11
- API Framework: FastAPI (async endpoints, dependency injection for DB session)
- ORM: SQLAlchemy (async) with Alembic for migrations
- Vector DB Client: qdrant-client (Python SDK)
- LLM + Embeddings: google-generativeai SDK (Gemini API)
- Data Validation: Pydantic v2 (all request bodies and response models must be typed)
- HTTP Client: httpx (for CoC and CR official API calls)
- Testing: pytest + pytest-asyncio

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = FOLDER STRUCTURE =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
/app
  /routers        → FastAPI routers (users.py, players.py, games.py, feedback.py)
  /agent          → Agent pipeline steps (assembler.py, assessor.py, retriever.py, planner.py, taxonomy.py)
  /services       → External service clients (gemini.py, qdrant.py, coc_api.py, cr_api.py)
  /db             → SQLAlchemy models (models.py) and session management (session.py)
  /schemas        → Pydantic request and response schemas (one file per domain)
  main.py         → FastAPI app entry point, lifespan events, router registration

/alembic          → Alembic migration files (never edit manually, generate via alembic revision)
/scripts          → One-time runner scripts (scraper.py, gap_fill.py, chunker.py, ingest.py, seed.py, test_retrieval.py)
/data
  /games          → Raw markdown strategy docs with YAML frontmatter (one folder per game)
/tests            → pytest E2E and edge case tests (test_e2e.py, test_edge_cases.py)
/docs             → README assets (demo.gif, architecture diagram source)

Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.env              → Never commit. Use .env.example for reference.
.env.example
requirements.txt
.cursorrules      → This file

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = FILE NAMING =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- All Python files: snake_case (e.g. coc_api.py, player_stats.py)
- Routers: named by domain (users.py, players.py, games.py, feedback.py)
- Schemas: named by domain (player_schemas.py, plan_schemas.py, game_schemas.py)
- Agent steps: named by function (assembler.py, assessor.py, retriever.py, planner.py)
- Scripts: named by action verb (scraper.py, ingest.py, seed.py, chunker.py)
- No abbreviations in filenames unless industry-standard (e.g. coc, cr are fine)

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = CODE STANDARDS =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- All FastAPI endpoints must be async def
- All database operations must use async SQLAlchemy sessions via Depends(get_db)
- All endpoints must declare a response_model= with a Pydantic schema
- All endpoints must have a description= and response_description= for Swagger
- No raw dicts as return values from endpoints — always return typed Pydantic models
- No hardcoded strings for game names, weakness categories, or skill tiers — use constants from agent/taxonomy.py
- No print() statements — use Python logging (logging.getLogger(__name__))
- No commented-out code — delete it or use git history
- Type hints on every function signature — no bare parameters without types
- Docstrings on every agent pipeline function (assembler, assessor, retriever, planner) — format: what it takes, what it returns, what external service it calls
- Error handling: all external calls (Gemini API, Qdrant, CoC API, CR API) wrapped in try-except with structured error logging
- All HTTPException responses must use the shape: {"detail": str, "step": str, "fallback_used": bool}

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = AUTH =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- NO authentication. NO JWT. NO OAuth. NO session tokens.
- User identity is passed as an integer user_id in the URL path (e.g. /players/{user_id}/stats)
- Never suggest adding auth middleware, auth dependencies, or token validation
- This is an intentional constraint — auth is handled in separate projects

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = DATABASE =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- ORM: SQLAlchemy async with asyncpg driver
- Connection string from env: POSTGRES_URL (format: postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@host:port/db)
- Session dependency: async generator in db/session.py, injected via Depends(get_db)
- Never write raw SQL strings — use SQLAlchemy ORM query syntax
- All schema changes via Alembic migrations only — never alter tables manually
- JSONB columns (seven_day_plan, loadout_recommendations, identified_weaknesses, stats_snapshot, improvement_delta) must be typed as dict or list in SQLAlchemy and Pydantic
- TEXT[] columns (retrieved_chunk_ids, preferred_weapons, known_weaknesses, goals, supported_modes) must be typed as List[str]
- Tables: users, games, user_profiles, player_stats, coaching_plans, progress_logs, feedback

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = QDRANT (VECTOR DB) =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Collection name: game_strategies (constant in services/qdrant.py — never hardcode elsewhere)
- Vector size: 768 (Gemini text-embedding-004 output dimension)
- Distance metric: Cosine
- Payload indexes exist on: game, genre, skill_level, weakness_category, weapon_class, experience_level
- All retrieval queries MUST include a game filter at minimum — never run an unfiltered search
- Payload filter format: use qdrant_client.models.Filter with FieldCondition and MatchValue
- Always deduplicate results by chunk_id before returning
- Cap merged results at 15 chunks maximum to stay within Gemini context window budget
- Store retrieved chunk_ids in coaching_plans.retrieved_chunk_ids for every plan generated (audit trail)
- Connection: host from QDRANT_HOST env, port from QDRANT_PORT env

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = GEMINI API =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Embeddings (primary): gemini-embedding-001 @ output_dimensionality=768
- Embeddings (alt if 001 TPM exhausted): gemini-embedding-2 (also free — verify dims before swapping Qdrant)
- Do NOT burn embedding-001 TPM on casual smoke tests when near limit
- Generation candidates (free tier the owner can use — test in this order when capacity is tight):
    1. gemini-2.5-flash-lite
    2. gemini-2.5-flash
    3. gemini-3-flash-preview   # "3 flash"
    4. gemini-3.1-flash-lite
    5. gemini-3.5-flash
- Current default GENERATION_MODEL in gemini.py: gemini-3.1-flash-lite (2.5-flash-lite often 503 under load)
- Prefer staying on Gemini for this portfolio; Grok only if ALL five generation free models fail
- CoC/CR live API: skip in routine testing if key IP allowlist is painful — assembler soft-skips live merge
- SDK: google-genai (Client API) — not the deprecated google.generativeai package for new code
- API key from env: GEMINI_API_KEY
- embed_text(text: str) → List[float] lives in services/gemini.py
- generate(prompt: str) → str lives in services/gemini.py
- All generation calls expect structured JSON output — always include "Return ONLY valid JSON, no preamble, no markdown fences" in every generation prompt
- Retry logic: retry once on JSON parse failure before falling back
- Batching for ingestion: 100ms sleep between embedding calls to respect rate limits

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = AGENT PIPELINE =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# The 4-step pipeline is the core of this project. Always preserve this sequence:
# Step 1 — assembler.py:  assemble_context(user_id, game_id, db) → dict
# Step 2 — assessor.py:   assess(context, db) → AssessmentResult
# Step 3 — retriever.py:  retrieve(assessment, context) → List[ChunkResult]
# Step 4 — planner.py:    generate_plan(context, assessment, chunks, db) → CoachingPlan

- Steps are called sequentially in routers/players.py inside POST /players/{id}/assess/{game_id}
- Each step is a separate module — never merge steps
- Weakness categories come from taxonomy.py — never hardcode category strings elsewhere
- Experience level branching (new / intermediate / experienced) happens ONLY in planner.py prompt construction
- Rejection history is fetched from feedback table in planner.py before building prompt
- Per-step timing must be logged at INFO level (helps demo and debugging)

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = WEAKNESS CATEGORY TAXONOMY =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Canonical source: agent/taxonomy.py — import from there, never redefine
# Shooter (cod, free_fire):            positioning | aim | game_sense | loadout | movement | team_comms
# Strategy/Mobile (coc, cr):           deck_building | resource_management | base_layout | troop_deployment | timing
# Open World (gta_v_online, rdr2):     mission_strategy | money_making | combat | stealth | progression

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = API ENDPOINTS — FULL LIST =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Users + Profiles
POST   /users
POST   /users/{id}/profile
GET    /users/{id}/profile/{game_id}

# Player Stats
POST   /players/{id}/stats
GET    /players/{id}/stats/{game_id}

# Core Agent Pipeline
POST   /players/{id}/assess/{game_id}          ← triggers full 4-step agent

# Plan Surface Endpoints
GET    /players/{id}/plan/{game_id}
GET    /players/{id}/plan/{game_id}/loadouts
GET    /players/{id}/plan/{game_id}/roadmap
GET    /players/{id}/plan/{game_id}/missions/today
GET    /players/{id}/plan/{game_id}/missions/{day}

# Progress Tracking
POST   /players/{id}/checkin/{game_id}
GET    /players/{id}/progress/{game_id}

# Freeform Ask (lightweight RAG, no full pipeline)
POST   /players/{id}/ask/{game_id}

# Feedback
POST   /feedback

# Live Data (CoC + CR only)
GET    /games/coc/player/{tag}
GET    /games/cr/player/{tag}

# Discovery + Health
GET    /games
GET    /games/{id}/topics
GET    /health

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = ERROR HANDLING =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- All HTTPException must use this JSON shape: {"detail": str, "step": str, "fallback_used": bool}
- step field identifies where in the pipeline the error occurred (e.g. "assembler", "assessor", "retriever", "planner")
- fallback_used: true if a fallback path was taken (e.g. empty retrieval fell back to tier-matched content)
- Add a global exception handler in main.py for unhandled exceptions — return HTTP 500 with structured body
- Specific guards:
    - No player_stats found → HTTP 400, step="assembler"
    - Gemini returns malformed JSON twice → HTTP 503, step="assessor" or step="planner"
    - Qdrant returns 0 results after fallback → HTTP 200 with fallback_used=true (not an error, a degraded response)
    - No active coaching plan for /plan/* endpoints → HTTP 404, step="plan_retrieval"

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = DOCKER =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Three services in docker-compose.yml: postgres, qdrant, api
- postgres: image postgres:16-alpine, port 5432:5432, volume postgres_data
- qdrant: image qdrant/qdrant:latest, ports 6333:6333 and 6334:6334, volume qdrant_data
- api: built from local Dockerfile, port 8000:8000, depends_on postgres and qdrant, env_file .env
- Dockerfile base: python:3.11-slim, install requirements.txt, uvicorn entrypoint
- All environment variables injected via .env file — never hardcoded in docker-compose.yml
- Startup order: docker compose up --build → alembic upgrade head → python scripts/seed.py → python scripts/ingest.py

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
POSTGRES_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://gamesage:gamesage@postgres:5432/gamesage
QDRANT_HOST=qdrant
QDRANT_PORT=6333
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
COC_API_KEY=your_key_here
CR_API_KEY=your_key_here
QDRANT_COLLECTION=game_strategies

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = PYDANTIC SCHEMAS =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Every endpoint must declare response_model= — no bare dict returns
- Nested JSONB fields must have their own Pydantic models (e.g. DailyMission, LoadoutRecommendation, SevenDayPlan)
- All Optional fields must have an explicit default (Optional[str] = None, not bare Optional[str])
- Use model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True) on all ORM-mapped schemas
- Request bodies: suffix *Create (e.g. PlayerStatsCreate, UserCreate)
- Response bodies: suffix *Response (e.g. CoachingPlanResponse, ProgressLogResponse)

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = TESTING (manual) =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Test every new endpoint with BOTH Swagger UI (http://localhost:8000/docs) AND curl
- Swagger first for quick iteration and schema inspection; curl to confirm real HTTP behavior
- Provide curl examples alongside Swagger when shipping a new endpoint
- PowerShell curl alternative: Invoke-RestMethod for GET; curl.exe for POST with -d / -H flags
- pytest E2E suite (Day 15) complements manual Swagger + curl testing — does not replace it
- Postman collection is Day 13 — until then, Swagger + curl are the manual test tools

