# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = GIT CONVENTIONS =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Commit after every individual feature — small, frequent commits
- Commit message format: type: short description
  - feat:    new feature or endpoint
  - fix:     bug fix or prompt tuning
  - chore:   setup, tooling, docker, dependencies
  - docs:    README, docstrings, swagger descriptions
  - data:    corpus files, seed data
  - test:    test files only
- Examples from this project:
  feat: skill assessment llm call with structured output and retry
  fix: retrieval quality tuning across game corpus
  chore: docker compose with postgres qdrant and api services
  data: scraped strategy corpus for coc cr rdr2 free fire

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# = WHAT TO AVOID =
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
- Never add authentication, JWT, OAuth, or session management — out of scope
- Never use synchronous SQLAlchemy — always async
- Never hardcode weakness categories or game names as string literals outside taxonomy.py and seed.py
- Never return raw dicts from endpoints — always use Pydantic response models
- Never run unfiltered Qdrant searches — always include at minimum a game filter
- Never commit .env — only .env.example
- Never use print() — use logging
- Never merge agent pipeline steps into a single file
- Never write raw SQL strings — use SQLAlchemy ORM
- Never add a frontend, React, or any UI — this is an API-only project
- Never suggest deployment (Render, Railway, Heroku, AWS) — local Docker only
- Never add Redis, Celery, or background task queues — out of scope for this project
- Never split a single strategy unit (one loadout, one deck, one base layout) across two chunks in the chunking pipeline